parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the sub-frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks and costly repairs.
symptoms: Rusting or corrosion of the sub-frame
particularly in the front end
flaking of paint
and signs of wear on the undercarriage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The flaking of paint can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the vehicle's appearance and potentially causing structural damage.
symptoms: Flaking or peeling of paint
particularly on the hood and roof
clear coat and paint peeling away
and underlying coat peeling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locking mechanism can cause inconvenience and potential safety risks, particularly if the doors cannot be opened or closed properly.
symptoms: Connecting rod from the door lever to the locks falling off
making it impossible to open the sliding door
doors cracking loose
and doors and windows leaking water inside when it rains.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped front brake rotors can cause the brakes to vibrate or pulsate, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal pulsates or vibrates
brake noise or grinding
uneven brake wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: Brakes lock up
vehicle skids or loses control
ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat track can cause the seat to move unexpectedly during a collision, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to the occupant.
symptoms: The seat moves or falls apart during a collision
the seat track breaks or cracks
the seat becomes loose or unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat structure can cause the seat to break or crack, compromising the safety and comfort of the occupant.
symptoms: The seat base or back cracks
the seat frame breaks
the seat becomes unstable or loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The interference with the seat belt can prevent its proper use, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to the occupant in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seat belt cannot be used due to interference from the armrest or other seat components
the seat belt is obstructed or restricted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to complete the headrest recall can lead to inadequate head and neck protection in the event of a collision, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to the occupant.
symptoms: The headrest recall is not completed due to unavailability of parts
the headrest is not properly secured or adjusted.
